FBIS4-63999 "drsov103_a_94021" FBIS-SOV-94-103 Daily Report 27 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS ITAR-TASS Reports U.S. Senate's Organized Crime Hearings ITAR-TASS Reports U.S. Senate's Organized Crime Hearings PM2705083194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 27 May 94 First Edition p 2 PM2705083194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [ITAR-TASS report: "United States Worried by Rising Crime in Russian Federation"] [Text] The unprecedented rise in organized crime in Russia poses a serious threat not only to its national security but also to the interests of Western countries, including the United States, according to participants in Wednesday's [25 May] hearings at the Permanent Subcommittee on Investigations of the U.S. Senate Committee for Governmental Affairs.
